Create a single executive PowerPoint slide titled 'Cloud infrastructure overview' with subtitle 'Azure · 3 environments · 14 subscriptions · 3 management groups · Dual-region active-active'. Organize the slide into 5 stacked sections separated by thin gray divider bars:
Section 1 — 'Network architecture — hub & spoke (per environment)': Two rows. Top row labeled 'Hub (connectivity & security)' with 5 boxes: Firewall (Traffic control), Bastion (Secure remote access), Front Door (Global load balancing), API gateway (Managed API layer), DevOps agents (Self-hosted VMSS). Bottom row labeled 'Spokes (application workloads)' with dashed border and 3 boxes: Container platform (AKS + Nginx ingress), Serverless functions (Azure Functions), Secrets management (Azure Key Vault). Connect hub to spokes with a small downward arrow.
Section 2 — 'Deployment & infrastructure': 3 equal boxes side by side: CI/CD pipelines (Azure DevOps — Code to build to deploy), Infrastructure as code (Terraform — All infra via pipelines), App packaging (Helm + Nexus registry — Versioned artifacts).
Section 3 — 'Security & compliance': 4 equal boxes side by side: Identity (Entra ID + PIM — Just-in-time access), Cloud security (Wiz CSPM — Posture management), Code scanning (Snyk SCA + SAST — Shift-left security), Observability (Azure Monitor + Splunk SIEM).
Section 4 — 'Resilience & availability': 2 wide boxes side by side: Dual-region deployment (Active-active — no single point of failure), Environment isolation (Dev / QA / Prod in separate management groups).
